  "text": "Traced the full admission webhook processing chain across kubernetes and api repos. The chain starts at Plugin.Admit()/Plugin.Validate() in the mutating/validating plugin.go files, which call generic.Webhook.Dispatch() in generic/webhook.go. This fetches hooks from the Source and delegates to the type-specific Dispatcher interface (defined in generic/interfaces.go). The mutating dispatcher (mutating/dispatcher.go) processes hooks sequentially with reinvocation logic tracked via webhookReinvokeContext (reinvocationcontext.go) - if a webhook mutates the object, previously-invoked webhooks with IfNeeded reinvocation policy are re-called. The validating dispatcher (validating/dispatcher.go) dispatches all matching hooks in parallel using goroutines with sync.WaitGroup. Both dispatchers use ShouldCallHook() from generic/webhook.go for rule/selector/match-condition filtering. The WebhookAccessor interface (accessors.go) provides a unified abstraction over v1.MutatingWebhook and v1.ValidatingWebhook with accessor implementations that cache parsed selectors and REST clients. The MutatingWebhookConfiguration and ValidatingWebhookConfiguration API types are defined in the api repo under admissionregistration/v1/types.go (and v1beta1/types.go).",
